frameDefinitions: An Agent saves a Patient or an Asset from a Harmful_situation.
A Grower endeavors to tend to and influence the environment of Food so as to foster its growth.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
Two or more distinct entities, which may be concrete or abstract objects or types, are characterized as being similar to each other.
A Mother and Father produce a Child or an Egg. 'Betty bore Gerry three intelligent daughters.'
This frame concerns the inception of the life of a Child, generally human, at a particular Time and Place.
frameExamples: Israeli commandos <t>rescued</t> the hostages and left.
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.

A mulberry is very <t>similar</t> in shape
to a loganberry
Little Jessie <t>came into the world</t> at 8 last night.
listRoleDefinitions: The sentient being who rescues the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen> from the <fen>Harmful_situation</fen>.
The living being who is rescued by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The entity that is judged to be valueable which might be lost or damaged by the <fen>Harmful_situation</fen>.
An event that occurs which could result in injury or harm to the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> rescues the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> rescues the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen>.
The <fen>Grower</fen> is the agent growing <fen>Food</fen>.

<fex name='Food'>Food</fex> is the item grown by the <fen>Grower</fen>, which can include things not traditionally eaten, like flowers, etc., or items for other consumption-related uses, like medicines, smokables, etc.
When the growing event occurs.
The greater geographic location where the <fen>Grower</fen> grows <fen>Food</fen>.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose similarity is at issue.

When there is an asymmetry, <fen>Entity_1</fen> is the entity characterized by its similarity to <fen>Entity_2</fen>, whose characteristics are assumed to be known.  <fen>Entity_1</fen> is often an external argument.

When the <fen>Entities</fen> are expressed separately, <fen>Entity_2</fen> is the one whose characteristics are assumed to be known; it serves as a basis for establishing characteristics of <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the entities is assessed.
A fact about <fen>Entity_1</fen> or the <fen>Entities</fen> that reveals how <fen>Entity_1</fen> is the same or different from other entities.  (Note the contrast with 'as to'.)
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the similarity occurs or exists.
The Place is the general area in which similarity occurs or exists
<fen>Mother</fen> is the female creature that produces the <fen>Child</fen>.
<fen>Child</fen> identifies the new self-motile creature produced from the <fen>Mother</fen> and <fen>Father</fen>.
<fen>Father</fen> is the male creature that copulates with the <fen>Mother</fen>, thus  leading to the birth of the <fen>Child</fen>.
<fen>Egg</fen> is an immobile object containing an organism that may hatch as a mobile, infant organism.
The <fen>Mother</fen> and <fen>Father</fen> expressed together.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
<fen>Child</fen> identifies the new self-motile creature.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the birth occurs, generally expressed as a date or a year.
The location where the <fen>Child</fen> enters the world.

<fex>Three foxes</fex> were saved from being savagely ripped apart.
She saved <fex>countless lives</fex> during her short stay on the plantation.
Three foxes were saved <fex>from being savagely ripped apart</fex>.
She saved my life on the bridge <fex>yesterday</fex>.
She saved my life <fex>on the bridge</fex> yesterday.
<fex>The two painters</fex> were alike in being unable to draw acceptably .
In the first phase <fex>Barthes's approach</fex> has similarities to that of Levi-Strauss.
The results of Method 2 show remarkable similarity <fex>to those obtained by Method 1</fex>
The disc announced Friday is <fex>physically</fex> similar to current music CDs
His presidency was different <fex>in that it offered a way forward for the common man</fex> .
Female clownfish lay <fex>their eggs</fex> around sea anemones
<fex>We</fex> are going to be having twins!
